title: Man's body discovered close to the University of Birmingham
text:
A man's body was discovered at a lake near Birmingham University Credit: ITV News Central Police have cordoned off a scene near the University of Birmingham after a man's body was found.
Officers were called to a lake on Edgbaston Park Road just before 3.30pm on Tuesday 21.
A large tent has been put up around the area while investigations continue. The body remains at the scene and is yet to be formally identified.
ITV News understands the incident does not appear to involve students or staff from the University of Birmingham.
Police say the death is being treated as unexplained.
